Offering views of the Mediterranean Sea, this polished hotel among shops is a 9-minute walk from Tangier Beach, 3 km from the Tangier Kasbah and 15 km from Tangier Ibn Batouta Airport.

    4/5
    Normally the name of Hilton hotel carries a lot of weight due to the brand efficiency quality and service but sometimes poor management brings negative feedback. …
    Normally the name of Hilton hotel carries a lot of weight due to the brand efficiency quality and service but sometimes poor management brings negative feedback.
    The rooms are excellently designed and serviced but lack of ventilation or access to fresh air make the rooms unbearable.
    The service is good but the management decisions on purchasing cheap quality toilet paper which I believe is a false economy making using toilet paper an uncomfortable experience.
    Being a five star hotel and not providing dental care????
    Late night the kitchen was closed and we could not order food in the restaurant while we were in the bar with a few friends.
    When we ordered some food from the MacDonald the reaction of some staff was out of character.
    All in all the hotel is fully furnished and decorated with good quality furniture and accessories. The swimming pool on the 13 floor is a place to be.
    Find me toffee nose but the food in the restaurant is average. I had better quality food outside.
    Please indulge for yourself and share your experiences for everyone.

    Of course, during all stay, we had access to the Executive lounge.
    Breakfast time
    This beautiful hotel is very comfortable and the view so great! Especially at breakfast time, you have 3 major criteria that makes you enjoying this very important time of each day:
    1) a true and warm, friendly welcome from the team from the very professional Assistant Manager, through the waiter al Mahdi, and Mounia who took care of my daily Moroccan crepes, heating them with a daily smile.
    2) Well, keep in bmind that the breakfast at Hilton Tangier is absolutely very good.
    3) Having a great breakfast with a so beautiful view of sea, under the sun, facing Spain coastline! There is nothing to compare!!!
    Swimming pool
    Weather was a bit cold to really and fully enjoying the swimming pool area. Let's say that during a sunny day, we made it! The water was hot, and again, as it is located on floor 13, few steps from the Executive lounge, you have the beautiful view. Windy, but really nice.
    A relaxing place
    Yes, this hotel is a relaxing one. I would say that if you really want to have a break, just enjoy it there. But I am sure that if.you need to work with all necessary amenities, everything is available. In my opinion, this hotel has been set for both: business and/or leisure. So make your choice.
    Respect of status
    From the beginning of our stay until the end, Diamond status was taken into consideration even if not all member of team were aware of the way it really works. But I know they did their best.
    Day-to day services
    A new hotel which need to run day-to-day operations. Confusion in what to provide to Diamond members implied to requesting bottle of water in the room, even missing bath towels, glasses... Nothing really important, but it took time to get what we were requesting.
    Finally, like many other travelers who experienced a stay, we are really happy. 10 minutes away from the old city by taxi, we absolutely loved our stay in Tangier, also thanks to this Hilton hotel.
    We are very very comfortable in recommending it without any hesitation. Great value, also thanks to this great team: Gishlane, Salam, Mounia, Al Mahdi, and all the others we did not name, who are carrying Morrocan hospitality that makes you feeling happy from breakfast time!

    About this hotel

    Offering views of the Mediterranean Sea, this polished hotel among shops is a 9-minute walk from Tangier Beach, 3 km from the Tangier Kasbah and 15 km from Tangier Ibn Batouta Airport. …

    Modern rooms feature free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, minibars, and tea and coffeemakers; some have sofabeds. Suites add living rooms. Upgraded quarters provide club lounge access with breakfast, drinks and snacks at no cost. Room service is available.

    Parking is free. There are 2 casual bars (1 with regular live music), as well as a chic 15th-floor restaurant with sea views. Other amenities include a rooftop pool and tapas bar, plus a gym and a sauna.
